Problem:
Let $z = 2 + \sqrt{2} - (3 + 3 \sqrt{2})i$, and let $c = 2 - 3i$.  Let $w$ be the result when $z$ is rotated around $c$ by $\frac{\pi}{4}$ counter-clockwise.

[asy]
unitsize(0.6 cm);

pair C, W, Z;

Z = (2 + sqrt(2), -3 - 3*sqrt(2));
C = (2,-3);
W = rotate(45,C)*(Z);

draw(Z--C--W);

dot("$c$", C, N);
dot("$w$", W, SE);
dot("$z$", Z, S);
label("$\frac{\pi}{4}$", C + (0.6,-1));
[/asy]

Find $w.$

Proposed Solution:
Step 1: Compute z − c
z = (2 + √2) − i(3 + 3√2), c = 2 − 3i
z − c = (2 + √2 − 2) + i[−3 − 3√2 + 3] = √2 − 3√2 i = √2(1 − 3i)

Step 2: Rotate by π/4
e^{iπ/4} = (1 + i)/√2
e^{iπ/4}(z − c) = √2(1 − 3i) · (1 + i)/√2 = (1 − 3i)(1 + i) = 4 − 2i

Step 3: Add c
w = c + e^{iπ/4}(z − c) = (2 − 3i) + (4 − 2i) = 6 − 5i

\boxed{6-5i}

